"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bvq1665702910898.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bvq1665702910898.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bvq1665702910898.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bvq1665702910898\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      How a Uniface Application Works\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__how_a_uniface_application_works_134009\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When developing Uniface applications it is important that you understand how Uniface processing works when the application is running so that you can influence application behavior appropriately.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__p_d43139e1_d43140e1_d43141e1\">Uniface can run applications in several ways, and each approach uses specific types of components:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__li_d21569e1_d21570e1_d21571e1\">Interactive desktop applications on Windows (GUI) or terminals (CHUI) use Form and Service components. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qjd1665702751029.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qjd1665702751029.html\" title=\"A Uniface desktop application is a traditional client/server application which can run on a local machine with access to remote functionality when needed.\">How a Desktop Application Works</a>.\n        </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__li_d21572e1_d21573e1_d21574e1\">Interactive web applications use Dynamic Server Page and Service components. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zwb1665702684890.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zwb1665702684890.html\" title=\"Uniface web applications run in a Uniface Web Application Server and are invoked by the client browser over the internet.\">Uniface Web Applications</a>.\n        </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__li_d21575e1_d21576e1_d21577e1\">Interactive mobile applications on Android or iOS use Dynamic Server Page (DSP) and Service components.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__li_d21578e1_d21579e1_d21580e1\">Static web application use Static Server Page (USP) and Service components.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__li_d21581e1_d21582e1_d21583e1\">Non-interactive (batch) process on various server platforms use Service and Report components.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__topic_d27752e1_d27753e1_d27754e1_d27755e1_d27756e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d460273e88\">\n Uniface Runtime Engine\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__p_d43142e1_d43143e1_d43144e1\">At the heart of a Uniface application is the Uniface Runtime Engine. It is responsible for instantiating components, interpreting user and system events, executing ProcScript, and communicating with the various types of connectors, such as a database connector and a network connector.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bvq1665702910898__p_d43145e1_d43146e1_d43147e1\">The runtime engine is built into the Uniface Server and Uniface executables.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526260\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526260\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "How a Uniface Application Works Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 How a Uniface Application Works When developing Uniface applications it is important that you understand how Uniface processing works when the application is running so that you can influence application behavior appropriately. Uniface can run applications in several ways, and each approach uses specific types of components: Interactive desktop applications on Windows (GUI) or terminals (CHUI) use Form and Service components. For more information, see How a Desktop Application Works . Interactive web applications use Dynamic Server Page and Service components. For more information, see Uniface Web Applications . Interactive mobile applications on Android or iOS use Dynamic Server Page (DSP) and Service components. Static web application use Static Server Page (USP) and Service components. Non-interactive (batch) process on various server platforms use Service and Report components. Uniface Runtime Engine At the heart of a Uniface application is the Uniface Runtime Engine. It is responsible for instantiating components, interpreting user and system events, executing ProcScript, and communicating with the various types of connectors, such as a database connector and a network connector. The runtime engine is built into the Uniface Server and Uniface executables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}